# scMultiMap

`scMultiMap` is a R package for inferring cell-type-specific peak-gene association with single-cell multimodal data. It provides an implementation for the statistical method scMultiMap proposed in this **paper link to-be-added**.

## Installation

`scMultiMap` is available on GitHub. You can install it using

``` r
## Load devtools for installing R packages from Github
library(devtools)
## Install CS-CORE from Github
install_github("ChangSuBiostats/scMultiMap")
```

## Vignettes

The [vignette](https://changsubiostats.github.io/CS-CORE/articles/CSCORE.html) shows an example of using scMultiMap for inferring peak-gene associations from 10x multiome data on PBMC.

